{"id":"2109.05856","submitter":"Mikhail V. Saramud","authors":"Maksim Kubrikov, Mikhail Saramud, Angelina Petetskaya, Evgeniy Talay","title":"Creation and Verification of Digital Twins in Cloud Production","comments":"6 pages, 2 figures, for icmtmte","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"cs.RO","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  This article discusses the use of digital twins for products made of polymer\ncomposite materials. The design of new products from polymer composite\nmaterials, both within the framework of the traditional and new direction of\ncloud production, requires the need to calculate the physical and mechanical\ncharacteristics of the product at the design stage. Carrying out full-scale\ntests increases greatly the cost and slows down the production. It requires the\nmanufacture of a prototype of the product. The use of existing development\ntools does not always provide the required characteristics. To solve this\nproblem, it is proposed to use a digital twin, which will not only solve the\nproblem, but will also help to move to cloud production and the development of\nthe Industry 4.0 direction. Thus, a new problem arises - how to create digital\ntwins of products from polymer composite materials. The analysis makes it\npossible to conclude that the traditional methods of mathematical physics are\nnot suitable for the solution of this problem, since the twins obtained with\ntheir help do not have any properties of adaptability. To solve the problem, it\nis proposed to use deep neural networks one of the most powerful methods of\nmachine learning. This will make it possible to obtain digital twins of\nproducts made of polymer composite materials that can adapt to changes in the\nmodel, environmental conditions and adapt to changes in the indicators of\nsensors and transducers installed on the product.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 13 Sep 2021 10:53:09 GMT"}],"update_