t from the data processing routines\nand/or metadata description implemented in REST, being the generic framework\ntools completely decoupled from dedicated libraries.\n  REST-for-Physics is a consolidated piece of software already serving the\nneeds of different physics experiments - using gaseous Time Projection Chambers\n(TPCs) as detection technology - for background data analysis and detector\ncharacterization, as well as generic detector R\\&D. Even though REST has been\nexploited mainly with gaseous TPCs, the code could be easily applied or adapted\nto other detection technologies. We present in this work an overview of\nREST-for-Physics, providing a broad perspective to the infrastructure and\norganization of the project as a whole. The framework and its different\ncomponents will be described in the text.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 13 Sep 2021 11:04:57 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 19 Nov 2021 15:46:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-02-09"}
